{"title":"{{< i18n wbs_dictionary >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n wbs_dictionary >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis WBS Dictionary provides a **detailed description of each WBS work\npackage**, defining:\n\n- Scope and boundaries\n- Key activities\n- Deliverables\n- Acceptance criteria\n- Responsible roles\n- Explicit exclusions\n\nThis document, together with the **WBS**, constitutes the **Scope Baseline** of\nthe project and must be approved **before finalization of the Project Management\nPlan (PMP)**.\n\n---\n\n## WBS Dictionary Structure\n\nEach entry includes:\n\n- WBS ID\n- Work Package Name\n- Description\n- Key Activities\n- Deliverables\n- Acceptance Criteria\n- Responsible Role(s)\n- Explicit Exclusions\n\n---\n\n## WBS Dictionary Entries\n\n### WBS ID: 1.1  \n\n**Work Package:** Initiation & Strategy  \n\n**Description**  \n\nDefines the strategic, environmental, and governance foundation of the project.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- Develop and approve Project Charter\n- Develop Business Case\n- Define Strategy & Governance (Value Stream, OKRs)\n- Identify and register stakeholders\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- Approved Project Charter\n- Approved Business Case\n- Strategy & Governance documents\n- Stakeholder Register\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- Formal sponsor approval\n- Alignment with SUB environmental strategy\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Project Sponsor (NOAA / SUB)\n- Project Manager\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Technical solution design\n- Model development\n\n---\n\n### WBS ID: 1.2  \n\n**Work Package:** Governance & Value Management  \n\n**Description**  \n\nEstablishes value measurement, KPI baselines, and decision governance.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- Define OKRs and KRs\n- Define executive KPIs\n- Establish KPI baselines and measurement methods\n- Define Stage‑Gate framework\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- OKR documentation\n- KPI framework\n- Stage‑Gate governance model\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- KPIs measurable and auditable\n- Ecological KPIs prioritized\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Product Owner\n- Project Sponsor\n- Environmental SME Lead\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Day‑to‑day project execution\n- Technical metric dashboards\n\n---\n\n### WBS ID: 1.3  \n\n**Work Package:** Data & Environmental Preparation  \n\n**Description**  \n\nPrepares subsea data and environmental context for safe AI usage.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- AUV image ingestion\n- Metadata and spatial data preparation\n- Image quality assessment\n- Definition of environmental annotation guidelines\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- Ingested and cataloged datasets\n- Quality assessment reports\n- Environmental annotation guidelines\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- Data completeness verified\n- SME approval of annotation guidelines\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Data Engineering Lead\n- Environmental SME Lead\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Model training\n- Automated decision-making\n\n---\n\n### WBS ID: 1.4  \n\n**Work Package:** AI Model Development  \n\n**Description**  \n\nDevelops the AI/CV capability for automated screening, under ecological\nconstraints.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- AI-assisted annotation (HITL)\n- Model training (binary classification)\n- Precision-oriented inference pipeline\n- Explainability mechanisms\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- Trained screening model\n- Inference pipeline\n- Model documentation\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- Meets minimum performance criteria\n- False-negative risk controlled\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Data Science Lead\n- Environmental SME Lead (validation)\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Full taxonomic classification\n- Autonomous decisions without validation\n\n---\n\n### WBS ID: 1.5  \n\n**Work Package:** Validation & Ecological Assurance  \n\n**Description**  \n\nEnsures ecological validity and risk control of automated screening.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- Model performance evaluation\n- Ecological validation by SMEs\n- Error analysis and mitigation\n- MVP ecological acceptance\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- Validation reports\n- Ecological acceptance decision\n- Risk mitigation actions\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- KPI‑3 (Ecological Data Protection Index) ≥ threshold\n- SME sign‑off\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Environmental SME Lead\n- Project Sponsor (acceptance)\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Scaling decisions\n- Operational deployment\n\n---\n\n### WBS ID: 1.6  \n\n**Work Package:** Digital Asset Consolidation  \n\n**Description**  \n\nTransforms project outputs into reusable corporate environmental assets.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- Dataset versioning\n- Model artifact management\n- Traceability and audit support\n- Reuse readiness assessment\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- Versioned datasets\n- Versioned model artifacts\n- Traceability documentation\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- ≥ 90% assets versioned and auditable\n- Governance approval for reuse\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Data Engineering Lead\n- SUB Data Governance\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Enterprise-wide rollout\n- External data sharing\n\n---\n\n### WBS ID: 1.7  \n\n**Work Package:** Project Management & Control  \n\n**Description**  \n\nProvides planning, monitoring, control, and closure of the project.\n\n**Key Activities**\n\n- Planning and monitoring\n- Risk and issue management\n- Communication and reporting\n- Project closure and lessons learned\n\n**Deliverables**\n\n- Status reports\n- Risk register updates\n- Closure report\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n\n- PMBOK compliance\n- Sponsor approval at closure\n\n**Responsible Roles**\n\n- Project Manager\n\n**Explicit Exclusions**\n\n- Technical execution\n- Environmental validation\n\n---\n\n## WBS Dictionary Governance Rules\n\n- Each work package has **one accountable owner**\n- Changes require formal change control\n- No work package may proceed past validation gates without ecological approval\n\n---\n\n## Scope Baseline Confirmation\n\nTogether, the following documents constitute the **Scope Baseline**:\n\n- Project Scope Statement\n- Work Breakdown Structure (WBS)\n- WBS Dictionary\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"format-links":["html","pdf"]},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","metadata-files":["../location/pt.yml"],"toc":true,"css":["../styles.css"],"html-math-method":"mathjax","embed-resources":true,"output-file":"wbs_dictionary.html"},"language":{"toc-title-document":"Índice","toc-title-website":"Nesta página","related-formats-title":"Outros formatos","related-notebooks-title":"Notebooks","source-notebooks-prefix":"Fonte","other-links-title":"Outros Links","code-links-title":"Ligações de código"